  Massachusetts-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement with modular
  covenant structure (non-compete, non-solicitation, non-dealing,
  non-investment, confidentiality, non-disparagement). Implements the
  Massachusetts Noncompetition Agreement Act, Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 149, § 24L
  (garden-leave or other agreed consideration, 12-month duration cap,
  formation-timing and notice requirements, excluded-worker categories,
  choice-of-law and § 24L(f) venue limits, and discretionary judicial
  reformation), and the profession-specific bans of Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 112, §§
  12X/74D/129B/135C and ch. 149, § 186. Generated by projecting the
  OpenAgreements restrictive covenant master to the Massachusetts overlay;
  drafted as a starting point for licensed counsel review.
